snippet: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu retained power, but his sharp-edged campaign raised questions about Israel’s future.
abstract: News Analysis; Israeli Prime Min Benjamin Netanyahu appears poised to retain power for fourth term, but his bitter re-election campaign inflicted deep wounds along the way; questions remain about his ability to heal Israel's internal strife or improve its standing in the world; yet Netanyahu has long history in power, and has shown he can switch from campaigning to governing, with record of being a pragmatist.

byline.contributor: Jodi Rudoren contributed reporting from Tel Aviv, Diaa Hadid from Nazareth, Israel, and Michael D. Shear from Washington.

lead_paragraph: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu retained power, but his sharp-edged campaign raised questions about Israel’s future.

headline.main: Deep Wounds and Lingering Questions After Israel’s Bitter Race
